  <source>Katholieke Universiteit Leuven</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The improvement in inspiratory muscle function might result in beneficial changes in
      breathing pattern during whole body exercise. The hypothesis is the effect of inspiratory
      muscle training as an adjunct to a pulmonary rehabilitation program improves the breathing
      pattern during an incremental cycle exercise.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
